---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Supported Sites | Ultra Zoom"
  description="Categorized list of sites Ultra Zoom hover-zooms out of the box, including image search, social, shopping, photography, and news sites."
  currentPage="sites"
  og={{
    url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/sites',
    title: 'Sites Ultra Zoom Supports',
    description: 'A categorized list of sites Ultra Zoom hover-zooms out of the box.',
    image: 'https://ultrazoom.app/images/icon-128.png',
  }}
>
    <main class="main page-content" id="main-content">
        <h1>Sites Ultra Zoom Supports</h1>

        <p class="pricing-intro">Ultra Zoom ships with optimized plugins for image-heavy pages across the open web, organized below by category. Most plugins are included in the free tier. A handful of sites that need special handling are <a href="/pricing">Ultra Zoom Pro</a> features and are marked <strong>(Pro)</strong> below. Beyond the bundled plugins, a community-maintained URL-rules pack auto-updates weekly to extend coverage to additional hosts without requiring an extension update. Don&rsquo;t see a site? Enable <em>All sites</em> mode in the popup for generic hover-zoom, or <a href="/contact">request a plugin</a>.</p>

        <section class="help-section" id="search">
            <h2>Search &amp; image discovery</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>Google Images</strong> &mdash; full-resolution previews from any image search.</li>
                <li><strong>Bing Images</strong> &mdash; same, on Microsoft&rsquo;s search.</li>
                <li><strong>DuckDuckGo Images</strong> &mdash; for the privacy-first crowd.</li>
                <li><strong>Yandex Images</strong> &mdash; especially useful for reverse image search workflows.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="social">
            <h2>Social networks</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>Reddit</strong> &mdash; preview gallery posts and image submissions without opening each one.</li>
                <li><strong>Twitter / X</strong> &mdash; full-resolution images from any timeline or quote.</li>
                <li><strong>Instagram</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; works on feed, profile, and explore views.</li>
                <li><strong>Facebook</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; preview photos in posts, comments, and album thumbnails.</li>
                <li><strong>Tumblr</strong> &mdash; great for art and photography blogs.</li>
                <li><strong>9GAG</strong> &mdash; faster scrolling on a meme-heavy feed.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="photography">
            <h2>Photography &amp; stock</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>Pinterest</strong> &mdash; pulls the largest source image, ideal for moodboards.</li>
                <li><strong>Flickr</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; full-size previews from photostreams and groups.</li>
                <li><strong>Imgur</strong> &mdash; native CDN handling for albums and direct links.</li>
                <li><strong>Unsplash</strong> &mdash; free stock photography, full-res preview.</li>
                <li><strong>Pexels</strong> &mdash; another free stock library with hover-zoom support.</li>
                <li><strong>Getty Images</strong> &mdash; preview at the largest watermarked size.</li>
                <li><strong>Alamy</strong> &mdash; same, for editorial and stock libraries.</li>
                <li><strong>Wikimedia Commons</strong> &mdash; license-friendly archive imagery.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="art">
            <h2>Art &amp; design</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>DeviantArt</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; original-resolution previews where the artist allows it.</li>
                <li><strong>ArtStation</strong> &mdash; portfolio thumbs to full-size in one hover.</li>
                <li><strong>Pixiv</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; multi-page illustration sets, sequenced via gallery navigation.</li>
                <li><strong>Behance</strong> &mdash; project covers and individual asset previews via the community URL-rules pack.</li>
                <li><strong>Dribbble</strong> &mdash; full-size shots from any feed via the community URL-rules pack.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="shopping">
            <h2>Shopping</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>Amazon</strong> &mdash; inspect product photos at full resolution before clicking through.</li>
                <li><strong>eBay</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; vital for triaging listings by photo.</li>
                <li><strong>Etsy</strong> &mdash; preview product images via the community URL-rules pack.</li>
                <li><strong>AliExpress</strong> &mdash; useful for product-listing screenshots and detail shots.</li>
                <li><strong>Avito</strong> &mdash; classified-ad photos at full size.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="auctions">
            <h2>Auctions &amp; collectibles</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>Catawiki</strong> &mdash; lot photos via the community URL-rules pack.</li>
                <li><strong>Heritage Auctions</strong> &mdash; same, for art and numismatics catalogues, via the community URL-rules pack.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="video">
            <h2>Video</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>YouTube</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; preview thumbnails and play videos in place.</li>
                <li><strong>Twitch</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; clip and stream-thumbnail previews.</li>
                <li><strong>Vimeo</strong> &mdash; thumbnail previews via the community URL-rules pack.</li>
                <li><strong>Bilibili</strong> &mdash; Chinese video platform with full thumbnail support.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="news">
            <h2>News &amp; reference</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>AP News</strong> &mdash; high-resolution editorial photography.</li>
                <li><strong>Wikipedia</strong> &mdash; click-free preview for any inline image.</li>
                <li><strong>Wikimedia Commons</strong> &mdash; archival images at original resolution.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="asia">
            <h2>Asia-focused platforms</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>Weibo</strong> &mdash; full-resolution previews on China&rsquo;s biggest social network.</li>
                <li><strong>Bilibili</strong> &mdash; covered above, also strong on photo posts.</li>
                <li><strong>Pixiv</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; multi-page sets navigated with arrow keys.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="dev-and-gaming">
            <h2>Code, gaming, and the rest</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>GitHub</strong> &mdash; preview attachments, screenshots, and avatars via the community URL-rules pack.</li>
                <li><strong>Steam</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; full-size promo art and screenshots from any store page.</li>
                <li><strong>LinkedIn</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; profile and post imagery at full size.</li>
                <li><strong>VK</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; photo posts and album previews.</li>
                <li><strong>TikTok</strong> <span class="badge-pro">(Pro)</span> &mdash; thumbnail and avatar zoom on profile and feed pages.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="more-sites">
            <h2>Even more, via the community URL-rules pack</h2>
            <p>Beyond the bundled plugins, the extension fetches a community-maintained URL-rules pack from <code>api.ultrazoom.app</code> every 7 days. The pack adds support for additional image hosts and sites without requiring an extension update, and Pro users also receive an extended Pro-only rules pack. The fastest way to see what&rsquo;s currently active is in the extension popup itself &mdash; <em>Plugins</em> tab.</p>
            <p>Need a site that isn&rsquo;t covered? <a href="/contact">Send us the URL</a> and we&rsquo;ll add a rule on the next pack publish, or a plugin in the next release. In the meantime, toggle <em>All sites</em> in the popup to enable generic hover-zoom on any domain.</p>
        </section>

        <p class="pro-cta">
            <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/ultra-zoom/jalclpdejbeamaamcpbolkclpnleagmg" class="pro-cta-btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Install free for Chrome</a>
        </p>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
